main event: A jet aircraft was reported to have exploded and the pilot parachuted out over Gold Beach, Oregon on September 28, 1960.
interesting points: The aircraft was estimated to be flying at an altitude of 8,000 feet when the possible explosion was observed.
The entire incident lasted only about 5 seconds, which the report notes is an unusually short duration for such an event.
Two F-89 aircraft were later vectored to the sighting area, but darkness prevented effective observation.
No known air traffic could be correlated with this observation.
The report notes that the observer was located approximately 5 miles from the aircraft.
sighted object: a jet aircraft that appeared to explode with the pilot parachuting out
